        "title": "The 15 Hats (ahem, Roles) of Social Workers",
        "excerpt":"          Social workers all wear a number of different hats, or function in a number of different roles for their practice. In this video we talk about 15 different roles that social workers frequently put on. We go through and talk talk about the roles of counselor, case manager, broker, enabler, enabler, educator, facilitator, mediator, negotiator, manager, analyst/evaluator, consultant, integrator/coordinator, spokesperson, organizer/mobilizer, and advocate.   References   Barker, R.L. (1995). The social work dictionary (3rd ed.). Washington, DC: NASW Press.   Yessian, M.R., &amp; Broskowski, A. (1983). Generalists in human-service systems: Their problems and prospects. Prentice Hall.   Zastrow, C., &amp; Kirst-Ashman, K. (1997). U_nderstanding human behavior and the social environment (4th ed.)_. Wadsworth Publishing Company.   Kirst-Ashman, K. K., &amp; Hull, Jr., G. H. (2015). Understanding generalist practice (7th ed.). Stamford, CT: Cengage Learning.   Chechak, D. (2008 November 10)The roles of a social worker. Retrieved from https://www.scribd.com/doc/7852257/The-Roles-of-a-Social-Worker  ","categories": ["Professional Blog","YouTube Videos"],
